						<summary>

						<p>Same slab [as in No. 147] in the Mahalingeśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">8th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This stone slab with an inscription of 1546 A.D., [see No. 147 above] seems to have contained an inscription of about the 8th century A.D. Very faint image of a few letters of this period can be made out on the back side of this record. Probably due to lapse of time and negligence the first engraving must have been damaged beyond recovery. Hence the slab has been used for engraving the present record. [A few cases of this type have come to light in some parts of Karnataka].</p>						

						</summary>
